<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[192,1440,1118,1208]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,323,1118,1142]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Gordon and Gonzalez" authorityYear="2019" box="[330,515,1118,1142]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Pentilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="muriel">
<emphasis box="[330,515,1118,1142]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Pentilia muriel</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is somewhat similar to other species with the same 
<typeStatus box="[1153,1206,1119,1143]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">type</typeStatus>
of dorsal color pattern, but is distinguished by a projection of basal border on the elytron with a projection inside of the humeral callus. The male genitalia also are distinct from those of similar appearing species.
</paragraph>
